testScript:
var dialerURL = 'https://<YOUR-AWS-LAMBDA-REST-API-HERE>';
var agentName = 'JohnDoe'
var sec = 1000;

client
    .rtcSetTestExpectation("audio.in == 1")
    .rtcSetTestExpectation("audio.out == 1")
    .rtcSetTestExpectation("audio.in.bitrate > 0")
    .rtcSetTestExpectation("audio.out.bitrate > 0")


function agentLogin(username){
    client
        .url(process.env.RTC_SERVICE_URL+'/callcenter/index.html')
        .rtcScreenshot("Agent screen")
    	.waitForElementVisible('body', 10*sec)
	    .setValue('input[name=friendlyName]',username)
	    .click('button[type=submit]')
	    .rtcScreenshot("Agent logged in")
}

function agentAcceptCall(){
    client
      .waitForElementVisible('td.accept-panel > button', 30*sec)
      .click('td.accept-panel > button')
      //In call
      .pause(25000)
       .rtcScreenshot("Agent in call")
      .click('button[ng-click="hangup()"]')
      .pause(1500)
      .click('button[ng-click="complete()"]')
       .rtcScreenshot("Agent hangup")
      }

function invokeIncomingCall(dialerURL) {
    client
        .pause(1000)
        .rtcActivateWebhook(dialerURL, {}, function(answer) { })
        .pause(1000);
}

//Code logic

agentLogin(agentName)
invokeIncomingCall(dialerURL)
agentAcceptCall()
name: Twilio Contact Center - Inbound Voice Calling
info:
This sample shows how to automate an inbound voice call for the Twilio Contact Center reference application.

We need a single probe here, which acts as the Agent who will receive the PSTN call from the customer.
